Males call all day long when the weather is rainy. Breeding occurs during the rainy season, between January and May. The males respond to intraspecific playbacks with shorter and more rapidly emitted note trills. Males are territorial, their small territories being spaced at least a few meters apart. Males usually call slightly above the leaf litter, exposed on a branch or a dead leaf. Eggs are deposited in the fold of a dead leaf (a single observation). This clutch was raised (
Fig. 6
) and some tadpoles were genotyped.
